Defendant Sharon M Gordon in court with attorney Mark Emil Kershek.  Kristi J Gordon appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty.  State makes sentencing recommendation.  Defense makes sentencing recommendation.  Steve G., defendant's husband, makes statement.  The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

9 MONTHS JAIL STRAIGHT (CREDIT - none);

TERM OF PROBATION:  1 YEAR(S);

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*No contact with:  Roseline M. unless initiated by victim
*Psychological evaluation and treatment deemed appropriate.

COURT COSTS:  $243.00 (apply cash bail; balance to be paid as a condition of probation);

DNA SURCHARGE:  Court waives the DNA Surcharge based on date of violation.

DRGOD:  $10.00 (apply cash bail; balance to be paid as a condition of probation);

CONDITION TIME: 30 days, STAYED; to be used at agent's discretion.  Agent to determine with or without non working hours.
